set and answer template\n    - Links the run_id\n    - Transitions task to `WaitingForRequirements` state\n    - Returns immediately (no fallthrough)\n  - `DispatchMode::Workflow` → falls through to standard lease claim/dispatch\n\n#### Issue 3: Watcher/Issue-Ingestion Adapter (FIXED)\n- **Status**: Complete implementation across multiple files\n- **Files**:\n  - `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/watcher.rs` - Trait and parsing logic\n  - `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/issue_watcher.rs` - FileIssueWatcher and InMemoryIssueWatcher implementations\n  - `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs` - Integration at lines 154-227\n- **Functionality**:\n  - Phase 1: `poll_watchers()` runs before each daemon cycle (line 161)\n  - Resolves dispatch mode from `/rb requirements draft/quick` commands\n  - Creates daemon tasks from watched issues via `create_task_from_watched_issue()`\n  - Handles idempotency via `issue_ref` + `source_revision` tracking\n  - Persists dispatch_mode on the task model\n\n### Additional Verified Components\n\n1. **Waiting-Task Resume Path** (Lines 229-352): After requirements run completes, next cycle:\n   - Checks `WaitingForRequirements` tasks\n   - Derives seed handoff if run is complete\n   - Populates task with project metadata\n   - Transitions to `Pending` for workflow dispatch\n   - Handles flow warnings when seed conflicts with routed flow\n\n2. **DispatchMode Enum** (model.rs):\n   - Added `RequirementsDraft` and `RequirementsQuick` variants\n   - Task model stores `dispatch_mode`, `source_revision`, `requirements_run_id`\n\n3. **Requirements Command Parsing** (watcher.rs, lines 29-68):\n   - Parses `/rb requirements draft` and `/rb requirements quick`\n   - Rejects malformed commands with explicit error\n   - Falls back to `Workflow` mode if no requirements command present\n\n4. **Conformance Coverage**:\n   - 97 CL